-- Hungary Stocks: OTP, Est Media Shares Move in Budapest Trading
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-07-05T15:17:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-05/hungary-stocks-mol-est-media-shares-move-in-budapest-trading.html
The benchmark  BUX (BUX)  index fell 0.5
percent to 17,311.96 by the close in Budapest.  The following were among the most active shares in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  ,  Hungary ’s largest lender, fell 1.3
percent to 3,561 forint. The country’s central bank warned the
government may miss revenue targets on a proposed financial
transaction tax. European stocks retreated as European Central
Bank President  Mario Draghi  said downside risks to the economy
remain.  Est Media Vagyonkezelo Nyrt. (ESTMEDIA HB), a Hungarian
entertainment company, fell 13 percent to 28 forint, a record
low. The company slid 14 percent yesterday after saying it
offered to sell a stake in Hungary’s biggest outdoor music
festival following a failed bond.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
